Map from M.I.A. Jailbreak, dated 29/12/2008.

Created by BlackOps and M.I.A, this is one of the very first maps for M.I.A. 24/7 Jailbreak. 

Los-Angeles encapsulates the flow that M.I.A. intended for his jailbreak server; fast-paced and extremely difficult for guards. Gun room has several easily reached access points, and the cell area is designed in a way so that clearing vent cell is a hard task. 

Even today Los-Angeles is one of the most popular maps in Australian Jailbreak (the only active server that retains an identical style to M.I.A. Jailbreak).

This map contains a basketball court, pool, soccer field, a large outside area with watch towers, and a kitchen.

Map from M.I.A. Jailbreak, dated 25/02/2009.

Created by dot.rich for M.I.A. 24/7 Jailbreak.

An edited version of the famous map Electric Razor (2007), it was intended to be the "ultimate" Jailbreak map and in terms of features blows all other M.I.A. maps out of the water. This map contains an obstacle course, laser game, 2 skipping arenas, a boxing arena, a vent cell, a map secret, kitchen, ice hockey, basketball, and a vessel of other vents snaking around the map.

This is a new map I've made in over a month. DE ROGER GOIS. What does this mean? Well, the meaning of the name is from a random player that joined and server and left. Although he never spoke and wasn't there for a long time, he was not forgotten. Thus, this map name was decided. I also wanted to make a map where bots could get hit by cars, but not endanger real players so this was fun. 

It's a small defusal map. The terrorists have taken over an old warehouse and are planning to destroy the gas station (the gois station) or blow up the water facility down the alleyway. Either way the walk will only be about 15-20 seconds. The counter-terrorists were called in to investigate after a car had crashed and after receiving a report of terrorists afoot hiding somewhere. So, they park their vehicles outside the gois station and check out the office. However, the building was closed and nobody was home, which leaves only the warehouse...  Good luck!

Disclaimer: I don't know how balanced this map is in PvP because it was made for adaptive bots, but feel free to give feedback. I imagine that no matter how many people play whichever team strategizes more will dominate either side of the map.

_sText:
made this map out of frustration from somewhat failing to make a different, higher quality map. I wanted to make something with an easy theme, so I decided to work on this. It's just an average map made for fun. 

The map itself is T3 and probably around 1:15:1:30. I haven't had any testers though so I could be off from that.

There are three bonuses
1st bonus: 10-20 seconds & slightly technical/climby
2nd bonus: 15-25 seconds & strafey
3rd bonus: 25-35 seconds & strafey but with some small climbs, surfs and boosters
If your server doesn't support multiple bonuses, I'd suggest the 1st bonus.
The map hasn't been tested by other people so if there are some dumb skips, lmk
